18:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Blue Prism is best suited for regulated industries, banking, government, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Nanonets, meanwhile, shines for finance teams, accounts payable, document heavy businesses, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2001, Blue Prism describes itself as \"Enterprise-grade intelligent automation with digital workforce management.\" Nanonets, established in 2017, positions itself as \"AI-powered intelligent document processing and data extraction.\" With 16 years between them, Blue Prism brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Nanonets offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
19:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Nanonets** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (10 vs 9), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Blue Prism is a poor choice — far from it. Blue Prism excels in its own right, particularly for regulated industries and banking.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent ocr and data extraction accuracy, go with Nanonets. If strong security and compliance focus matters more to you, Blue Prism is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
